:[{"type":"text","text":"Why is it important to listen to teachers during a fire drill?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Spatial Sense"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Children develop an understanding of spatial sense by using positional words and phrases, such as “beside,” “up,” and “down.” Practicing with these words develops spatial awareness. Connect the positional words in the book to real life examples by using the same phrases throughout the day. "}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_2","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Healthy me "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":" WEEK 4: Safe and Sound"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Mind Builder: Move Carefully Through Surroundings"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Explain to children that their surroundings are the things and people all around them. Talk about how moving carefully can be important to not hurt yourself or the people around you. Help children come up with examples of when you might be more careful, like if something is hot or easy to break, and model careful movements. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"elemen