ext":"We’ll use our Mind Builder of moving carefully to learn more about how to be careful with our bodies during a fire drill."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Review "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"carefully"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 4"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"It says “be quiet, listen to the teacher.” Why is it important to hear what the teacher is saying? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 14–15"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The children are in a line beside each other. Why do the children need to be careful of each other’s bodies when they are beside each other? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Review "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"beside"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 16–17"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Why is it important not to run or talk during a fire drill? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 20–21"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The boo