"name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Read-Aloud: Focus on Classification"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 8–9"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What do the children do? What do the adults do? Let’s count adults."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s use red Connecting Cubes to help us count. We’ll use one red cube to stand for each adult."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"count"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use red Connecting Cubes."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 14–15"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What does this adult do when the fire drill starts? What do the children do?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 16–17"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The children line up quickly and quietly. Let’s count the children we see. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s use blue Connecting Cubes to help us count. We’ll use one blue cube to stand for each child."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use blue Connecting Cubes."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 18–19"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The children are walking in pairs. Let’s arrange our cubes into pairs."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pairs"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How does being part of a pair change how they move? How does it help with safety? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 26"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What does the teacher count? Why do you think the teacher counts the children? What do the children do? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 28–29"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s make a graph using the red and blue Connecting Cubes we counted to find out if there are more adults or children in the class."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"There are a lot more children! Why does that make it more important for the children to listen and be quiet?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Talk About It"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Did you listen and remember as we read the story today? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_guiding-question_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How do we keep track of all the children during a fire drill?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Possible responses:"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We stay with buddies."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We listen to the adults."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We call out each child’s name."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Interactive Writing"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share a pen with children as you draw and write together about how to stay safe during a fire drill."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Support"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What do you do with buddies during a fire drill?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We stay with b"},{"type":"element","name":"fill-in-the-blank","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"____"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(buddies)"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We stay with buddies."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenge"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Why is it important to keep track of everyone? What else can we do to stay safe?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Being Safe"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Safety drills can be worrying for many children. Help children cope by providing context (fires rarely happen) and showing patterns of behavior (practicing fire drills). Role-playing situations, like fire drills, give children situational context and shows them what to expect. It can also help to explain the unlikeliness of a real emergency."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_4","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"healthy me"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 4: Safe and Sound"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_4","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Talk About Being Safe"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Discuss the importance of being careful with your body. Help children make a list of the things they can do to stay safe in the classroom. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_4","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"People Graph "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Make a real-life pictograph with the children acting as the pictures! Choose an easily-visible attribute like short/long hair to create two types of data to compare. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_4","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce two new words. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 5.4.4 Vocabulary Cards."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"jumping little"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Big Chart of Big Ideas"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show Big Chart 5.4.4"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This week we are going to read "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Five Little Froggies Jumping on the Bed."}]},{"type":"text","text":" It is a song about frogs who are not being safe."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect the Texts"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Fire Drill"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Five Little Froggies Jumping on the Bed"}]},{"type":"text","text":" both focus on being safe. Let’s look for connections between them aswe read."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Fire Drill "}]},{"type":"text","text":"book cover."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit the Concept Question"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How can we protect ourselves and our bodies?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close-Read: Connect to Safe and Sound"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s sing the song together!"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Sing the song with the children and then review the pictures. Ask questions and use Equity Sticks to choose children to respond."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_prompt","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Five little froggies"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The frogs are jumping on the bed. Are they are being careful with their bodies when they jump? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Review "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"jumping"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_prompt","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Four little froggies"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What happened? What did Mama do? What did the doctor say? The doctor is telling Mama how to keep the little froggies safe!"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Review "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"little"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_prompt","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Three little froggies"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Were the frogs being safe? Did they listen to what the doctor said? Why should you listen to what the doctor tells you?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_prompt","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"No more froggies"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Where are all of the frogs? What are they doing on the bed now? Are they being careful with their bodies? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What can the frogs do to protect themselves and their bodies?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended Play"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Make frog stick puppets using found objects like buttons for eyes and paper plates or lunch bags for the body. Provide green paint and coloring supplies, and encourage children to use their imaginations to make their own little froggies. Once children have completed their puppets (and they’ve dried properly), sing the song again with all of the children holding their froggies."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Guided Writing"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide a writing prompt about how to move safely and give feedback as children draw and write in response to the prompt."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Graphing"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Children first learn about classification by sorting. Graphing allows for children to begin more complex classification. Simple bar graphs can help children interact with visual information, work together, and learn from each other."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_5","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"healthy me"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 4: Safe and Sound"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Connect to Health"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Guide children to think about what they learned about safety. Help them make the connection between being safe and healthy habits like eating well and brushing teeth."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Sing About Moving"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Sing and dance to the "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Hokey Pokey"}]},{"type":"text","text":", but vary the location words by verse. In addition to "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"in"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"out,"}]},{"type":"text","text":" use "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"up"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_emphasis","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"down"}]},{"type":"text","text":". Ask children to supply other pairs of location words."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_5","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce new vocabulary. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 5.4.5 Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"between"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit the Book"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the book cover."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s retell and reenact the book "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Fire Drill "}]},{"type":"text","text":"by Paul DuBois Jacobs and Jennifer Swender, and illustrated by Huy Voun Lee."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Lala Stick Puppet."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Who remembers if this book tells us a story or teaches us information?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Guiding Question"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We read about how children should behave during a fire drill. When we read today, I want you to think about this question:"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_guiding-question_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How do fire drills help us stay safe?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Read-Aloud: Retell and Reenact"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s reread the book one more time together. This time, we will act out the fire drill with the children in the story."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 4"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s follow each of the steps of the fire drill rules one at a time."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"First let’s all be quiet. Shhh!"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Now follow my directions. Everyone stand up carefully. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s get in a line. When you are in line, check and remember who you are between. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Review "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"between"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Remember to move quickly, quietly, and carefully. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that we are all in a line, we are going to walk around the classroom. Look at what you are near."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Now we will stay in one place until an adult says to go back."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Time to go back! Stay quiet and move carefully until we are back."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Great job, everyone!"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 10–11"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"On the count of three, we will sound like bells for five seconds. Stop when I raise my hand. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 22–23"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The children each listen for their names, then raise a hand and say, “Here I am!” I want everyone to raise a hand. Let’s call out, “Here I am!” "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"page 32"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The class in the story has a fire drill, but there are other types of drills too. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Review your class’s procedures for other types of drills you practice, like earthquake, tornado, or sheltering in place."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Talk About It"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask the guiding question again:"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_guiding-question_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How do fire drills help us stay safe?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Possible responses:"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We learn what to do if there is a real fire."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bulleted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"They teach us how to move carefully."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Independent Writing"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Invite children to draw or write a story about a fire drill."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Support"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How should you walk during a fire?"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"During a fire you should walk c"},{"type":"element","name":"fill-in-the-blank","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"____"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(carefully)"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_numbers","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"During a fire you should walk carefully."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_support_challenge-box","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_hed_support-challenge","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Challenge"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What other safety drills do we practice?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Multilingual Learners"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual support and gestures can help multilingual learners become comfortable with location terms. Action songs like Hokey Pokey and pointing out real-world examples in context can help support their acquisition of words to foster spatial sense."}]}]}]}]}]}]}]